rials, portrait busts to imperial pageants, tropical plants to cartoons made by artists on the spot, copies of paintings from ancient caves in India to 1950s film. Essays do not simply catalogue and collect this eclectic congregation, but provide new ways for assessing the significance of the Sydenham Crystal Palace for both nineteenth- and twentieth-century studies. The volume will be of particular interest to researchers and students of British cultural history, museum studies, and art history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aModernism (Art). 7aSCIENCE / History.2bisacsh  aClass.  aCrystal Palace.  aEducation.  aEmpire.  aExhibitions.  aLeisure.  aMaterial culture.  aNation.  aSydenham.  aVisual culture.1 aBoaden, James, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEarle, Nic, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEdwards, Jason, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHales, Shelley, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHunt, Verity, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKeene, Melanie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNichols, Kate, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNichols, Kate, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRoberts, Ann, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTurner, Sarah Victoria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTurner, Sarah Victoria, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2017 eBook-Packagez978311128281740uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152611493840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526